com.twiddles.ganesha.functionality
Interface RDFObject

All Known Implementing Classes:
JenaObject
public interface RDFObject

Interface for querying the object of an RDF resource's property. The object of a property statement about a resource can be a literal value, another resource or a container.

See Also:
RDFResource, RDFContainer

getObjType

int getObjType()
Query the type of this RDF object. The returned value can be compared to the constants defined in this interface to determine of what type the object is.

Returns:
object type code
See Also:
LITERAL, RESOURCE, BAG, SEQ, ALT, UNKNOWN

getLiteral

java.lang.String getLiteral()
Retrieve the literal value. If this object is of type literal then the value will be returned. Otherwise null will be returned.

Returns:
value or null
